results.name: Air Max 90 Leather GS 'White Turf Orange Speckled'
results.story: Crafted for big kids, the Nike Air Max 90 Leather GS ‘White Turf Orange Speckled’ features a mostly neutral palette with sharply contrasting accents. Traditional mesh construction is discarded in favor of an all-leather upper in black, white and grey tones. The sneaker’s lower TPU eyelets are rendered in a bright orange hue, matching the waffle-traction rubber outsole. A blue-tinged Max Air unit supplements the speckled foam midsole while also providing a cooling burst of color.

results.name: Flex Runner GS 'Game Royal'
results.story: Developed for big kids, the Nike Flex Runner GS ‘Game Royal’ showcases a gradient blue finish on a versatile slip-on built for play. The stretchy sock-like mesh upper is reinforced with no-sew overlays and a midfoot cage with elastic straps that wrap over the tongue and around the heel. Dual webbing pull tabs provide easy on and off. The vibrant blue and crimson hues up top are offset by a solid white foam sole, featuring flex grooves underfoot for a smooth ride.

results.name: Air Max Excee PS 'Iron Grey Game Royal'
results.story: Built for little kids, the Nike Air Max Excee PS ‘Iron Grey Game Royal’ highlights vibrant accents on a lifestyle runner inspired by the Air Max 90. The sneaker utilizes a breathable grey mesh upper with tonal leather overlays at the forefoot and heel. Contrast stitching in Volt lines the edges of the grey suede saddle, partially obscured by a royal blue leather Swoosh. The latter hue is repeated on cassette detailing that frames the Volt-colored Max Air unit nestled in the heel.

results.name: Flex Advance PS 'Black White'
results.story: Offered in little kid sizing, the Nike Flex Advance PS ‘Black White’ applies an essential two-tone palette to a versatile slip-on built for everyday wear. Nike FlyEase technology replaces traditional laces with an extra-wide opening, pull tabs at the tongue and heel, and two hook-and-loop straps that crisscross over the vamp. The black textile upper is reinforced with a synthetic toe cap and mounted on a contrasting white foam sole unit. Underfoot, durable rubber is placed in high-wear areas for grippy traction.

results.name: Kyrie Flytrap 4 PS 'Summit White Purple Pulse'
results.story: Crafted for little kids, the Nike Kyrie Flytrap 4 PS ‘Summit White Purple Pulse’ showcases a pristine finish with subtle pastel accents. Elastic laces combine with an adjustable hook-and-loop ankle strap to secure the basketball-inspired mid-top, featuring an upper built with textile and synthetic materials. A mesh tongue enhances the shoe’s breathability, while a fabric-lined padded collar delivers a comfortable fit. The sneaker rides on a full-length foam midsole, supported underfoot by a translucent lavender outsole that extends up the sidewalls for added traction.

results.name: Team Hustle D10 PS 'University Red'
results.story: Built for little kids, the Nike Team Hustle D10 PS ‘University Red’ dresses the basketball-inspired sneaker in an essential two-tone color scheme. The crimson mesh upper is accented with contrasting black hits on the Swoosh, tongue and elastic laces. The latter works in concert with an adjustable hook-and-loop ankle strap to deliver a custom fit. Soft cushioning arrives via a full-length foam midsole, supported by a durable rubber outsole marked with a large ‘X’ — a nod to the 10th edition of the Hustle D line.

results.name: Question Mid Big Kid 'I3 Motorsports'
results.story: The Reebok Question Mid Big Kid ‘I3 Motorsports’ carries an upper that combines matte black synthetic leather with shiny metallic silver accents, a dynamic that mirrors the two-tone finish commonly featured on ATVs and dirt bikes. Allen Iverson’s Question logo is embroidered on the heel tab, complementing Reebok Vector branding on the quarter panel and tongue, the latter featuring mesh construction for enhanced airflow. The sneaker rests on a foam midsole with sculpted sidewalls that mimic the Hexalite cushioning of the original.

results.name: Question Mid Little Kid 'I3 Motorsports'
results.story: The Reebok Question Mid Little Kid ‘I3 Motorsports’ features a two-tone finish inspired by ATVs and dirt bikes, which frequently use a high-contrast matte finish with gloss detailing. An integrated lacing system secures an upper built with black synthetic leather. Reebok Vector branding is embroidered on the quarter panel and tongue, featuring open mesh construction for improved breathability. A polished metallic silver finish distinguishes the mudguard and toe cap. Underfoot, a smoky rubber outsole provides durable traction.

results.name: Team Hustle D10 FlyEase PS 'Black Metallic Silver'
results.story: Built for little kids, the Nike Team Hustle D10 FlyEase PS ‘Black Metallic Silver’ applies an essential two-tone palette to a basketball-inspired mid-top. The black mesh upper is secured with elastic laces and a hook-and-loop strap connected to a wraparound heel zipper, which opens up and allows feet to easily slip in or out. On the lateral side, an oversized metallic silver Swoosh dips below the cushy foam midsole. A durable rubber outsole is marked with a large ‘X,’ marking the 10th installment of the Team Hustle D series.

Air Max 270 PS 'Light Smoke Grey Crimson'
results.colorway: Light Smoke Grey/Dark Smoke Grey/Bright Crimson/White
results.story: Crafted for little kids, the Nike Air Max 270 PS ‘Light Smoke Grey Crimson’ spotlights the sneaker’s buoyant cushioning technology. Nestled under the heel, the large-volume Max Air unit is tinted in a bright red hue, matching the glossy TPU heel counter that reinforces the grey mesh upper. An integrated lacing system works in tandem with a stretchy neoprene bootie to deliver a snug, comfortable fit. Heritage-style branding on the exaggerated tongue gives the nod to the classic Air Max 180 from 1991.

results.name: CLOT x Air Max 1 PS 'Kiss of Death' 2021
results.story: Built for little kids, the 2021 reissue of the CLOT x Nike Air Max 1 PS ‘Kiss of Death’ brings back a coveted collaboration from 2006 — the first ever joint effort between the Swoosh and Edison Chen’s streetwear brand. Updated with refreshed details, the sneaker’s standout features remain intact, including a transparent toe box, scaly red leather Swoosh and deconstructed ostrich-skin collar. They’re joined by a reflective heel overlay in red leather, along with upgraded reflexology-inspired graphics on the custom sockliner and translucent rubber outsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 5 Retro PS 'Stealth 2.0'
results.story: The Air Jordan 5 Retro PS ‘Stealth 2.0’ brings back a 2006 colorway in little kid sizing. The mid-top silhouette features a tumbled white leather upper with semi-translucent netting on the quarter panels and light grey molded eyelets. A royal blue Jumpman adorns a silver reflective tongue, matching the sneaker’s lace locks and collar lining. A second Jumpman icon is embroidered on the back heel. This scaled-down edition features a full-length foam midsole that lacks the visible Air heel unit of the original.
